article.headline: Bucknell 63, Binghamton 60
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Bryan Cohen scored 16 points, Patrick Behran added 15 and Justin Castleberry hit two free throws in the final seconds Tuesday night, leading Bucknell to a 63-60 victory over Binghamton in the teams' first meeting. Darryl Shazier added 11 points and Castleberry, whose two free throws with four seconds left provided the final three-point margin, had five points for Bucknell (2-6), which snapped a three-game losing streak. D.J. Rivera had 21 points and nine rebounds, Reggie Fuller added 17 points and Malik Alvin scored 12 for Binghamton (4-3), which missed all 16 of its 3-point shots in the loss.
